4:
Selgir from
The-Island-at-the-End-of-the-Sea?
You're under arrest for desertion of
your post!
12:
Selgir was formally discharged. We
know he is guilty of no crime!
14:
In the Navy, if there's no records of it,
it didn't happen.
22:
Wait, Nimbus. Let's hear what they
have to say.
25:
So. You here because you have a
job for me?
27:
Hah. You've always been a
reasonable man, Selgir.
28:
Everyone else, scram! This has got
nothing to do with you!
32:
We are Selgir's allies. His business is
our own.
35:
Where'd you get the circus animal,
Selgir?
37:
Don't wanna answer? Fine. We're not
here for small talk.
38:
You are gonna find Jolly Jack's
treasure for us. And that's a
command.
41:
You believe in the myths about Jolly
Jack's trove?
42:
Even if they are true, why send me?
Go hire a salvager.
45:
Don't play dumb with us. We know
you were chummy with one of Jolly
Jack's descendants. What's more,
we know he told you where the gold
is.
46:
If you won't tell us, we'll just ask the
sailors under your command.
49:
...Fine. But if you want me to go on
this treasure hunt, get me a ship
and crew.
51:
Deal. What you're gonna fetch for
me is worth far, far more.
57:
We're sorry. We've been nothing
more to you than extra baggage.
59:
First Bragé, now this. Starting to think
the government has more pigs than
people.
61:
Seems those men were demoted.
And that resentment's the only thing
keeping them from crawling back to
Gaea.
62:
They must be real desperate if they
gave us all these resources to chase
an old wives' tale.
84: I'll be taking this as a tip.
86:
Sure, sure, help yourself! Consider it
hush money.
94:
I couldn't care less about the gold
and jewels. Not worth letting 'em use
us like that!
97:
Yeah... That money could've gone to
someone who needed it. Now all it's
gonna do is make fat pigs even
fatter.
99:
Knowing them, they're going to be
busy keeping this loot a secret.
101:
They're so blinded by greed, they
didn't even notice the chests were
bugged. Pretty soon, the
government's gonna know them
better than their own mothers.
108:
Captain... Don't tell me you did it for
us.
112:
Only thing I could think of. But you're
on your own from here.
118:
There's one last thing I need to take
care of. Follow me.
125: Here. I found it in the trove.
128:
Never saw him without it. You know
what it is, right?
131:
The locket with my portrait, yes...
Hehe. Oh dear, it must seem terribly
old-fashioned now.
132:
Thank you, Selgir. Will you be setting
sail soon?
135:
Yeah. My new friends are waiting for
me.
141:
Sure you don't want to stay any
longer?
146:
Why don't we all have a drink
tonight? I'm in the mood for
company.
150: I'll bring the tea and juice.
